==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nodal
<hw>Nod"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of the nature of, or
relating to, a node; <as>as, a <ex>nodal</ex> point</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Nodal line</b></col>, <col><b>Nodal
point</b></col></mcol>, <cd>in a vibrating plate or cord, that line or
point which remains at rest while the other parts of the body are in a
state of vibration.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nodated</ent>⟦br⟧
